statements: CREATE TABLE analytics_data (id INT PRIMARY KEY, event_name VARCHAR(255), event_value INT, event_date DATE)
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS analytics_data (id INT PRIMARY KEY, event_name VARCHAR(255), event_timestamp TIMESTAMP)
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS user_data (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_name VARCHAR(255), user_email VARCHAR(255)
CREATE TABLE pageviews (id INT PRIMARY KEY, page_url VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE users (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(100));
CREATE TABLE events (event_id INT PRIMARY KEY, event_name VARCHAR(50), timestamp TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE analytics.users ( user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(255), email VARCHAR(255), created_at TIMESTAMP )
CREATE TABLE analytics.products ( product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(255), category VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10,2) )
CREATE TABLE analytics.orders ( order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, product_id INT, order_date DATE, quantity INT )
CREATE TABLE Sales (id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT, amount INT, sales_date DATE)
